%h1(id="catalogue" style="margin-top:0") 
.section-grouping
  %h2 1. Create a Catalogue

  %p
    To create a deployable XML file first you must create a catalogue.  

  %p
    %ol
      %li
        In the Aeolus web interface, go to
        %b Administer
        &rArr; <b>Content</b>.

      %li
        Click the "New Catalog" button. Give your catalog a name, associate it with the Default pool, and save it.

      %li
        Click on the name of your new catalog.  

  %p
    %center
      %a{ :href => "Images/Start Instance Images/catalog.png",
          :target => "_blank" }
        %img.thumbnail{ :src => "Images/Thumbnails/catalog_thumb.png",
              :title => "Testing Image - click to view at full size in a new window",
              :alt => "Testing Image - click to view at full size in a new window" }

%h1(id="deployable" style="margin-top:0") 
.section-grouping
  %h2 2. Create the Deployable

  %p
    This section dictates the instructions for creating the deployable. Once you have pushed an image to a provider, you are able to create a deployable.
  %ol 
    %li
      Once you have uploaded an image, you want to push this image.
    %li
      While you are pushing this image, there is an option in the right hand corner that says, 'Create Deployable from Image'. Click this.
    %li
      Indicate the name, hardware profile and the catalog then click, save.

    %p
      %center
        %a{ :href => "Images/Start Instance Images/deployable_image.png",
            :target => "_blank" }
          %img.thumbnail{ :src => "Images/Thumbnails/deployable_image_thumb.png",
                :title => "Deployable Image - click to view at full size in a new window",
                :alt => "Deployable Image - click to view at full size in a new window" }


    %li
      You will be redirected to the deployable page where you will be able to launch your image.

%h1(id="deployable" style="margin-top:0") 
.section-grouping
  %h2 3. Creating a Custom Deployable
  
  %p
    You are able to also create a custom deployable.
  %p
    %ol
      %li        
        Click on the New Deployable button.  Give your entry a name, description, and upload the deployable XML file you created.  Save your new deployable.

      %li
        In the Aeolus web interface, go to the
        %b Monitor
        tab.
        %br
        Under "Your Pools" is the default pool. On the right side
        of the default pool there's an arrow. Click the arrow and it will expose the
        button "New Deployment". Click the "New Deployment" button:
        %br
        %br

        %center
          %a{ :href => "Images/Start Instance Images/new_deployment.png",
              :target => "_blank" }
            %img.thumbnail{ :src => "Images/Thumbnails/new_deployment_thumb.png",
                  :title => "New Deployment - click to view at full size in a new window",
                  :alt => "New Deployment - click to view at full size in a new window" }
        %br

      %li
        Give your deployment a name and upload the deployable you just created.
        Click the
        %b Next
        button where you will begin to launch your deployment.

%h1(id="launch_deployment" style="margin-top:0")
.section-grouping
  %h2 4. Launching a Deployment

  %ol
    %li
      To launch the deployment click the "Launch" button.

    %br
      %center
        %a{ :href => "Images/Start Instance Images/launch_deployment.png",
            :target => "_blank" }
          %img.thumbnail{ :src => "Images/Thumbnails/launch_deployment_thumb.png",
                    :title => "Launch Deployment - click to view at full size in a new window",
                    :alt => "Launch  Deployment - click to view at full size in a new window" }
      %br

    %li
      Aeolus will then launch an instance of the template, using the AMI
      created on the previous page.
    %li
      The main view will list your instances, with the message
      "<em>Deployment launched.</em>" near the top:

    %li
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %center
        %a{ :href => "Images/Start Instance Images/instance_added.png",
            :target => "_blank" }
          %img.thumbnail{ :src => "Images/Thumbnails/instance_added_thumb.png",
                :title => "Instance 1 added",
                :alt => "Instance 1 added" }

    %li
      Within a minute or two, the
      %b State
      field for the instance should change to "<em>running</em>". The state will automatically be updated on the page;
      there is no need to refresh the page.

    %li
      If you are using Amazon EC2, follow the next steps to complete your configuration.
  %br


